      <ul>
        {{(g)}}
        \item The equation has no solution.
      </ul>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      {{ <xref ref="exer_sec74-4"></xref>.}}
      \item
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            The statement is false.
            By using the multiplication table for <m>\mathbb{Z}_6</m>,
            we see that a counterexample is <m>\left[ a \right] = \left[ 2 \right]</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            The statement is true.
            By using the multiplication table for <m>\mathbb{Z}_5</m>,
            we see that:
            <ul>
              \item <m>\left[ 1 \right] \odot \left[ 1 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]</m>. \item <m>\left[ 2 \right] \odot \left[ 3 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]</m>. \item <m>\left[ 3 \right] \odot \left[ 2 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]</m>. \item <m>\left[ 4 \right] \odot \left[ 4 \right] = \left[ 1 \right]</m>.
            </ul>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      {{ <xref ref="exer_squaresinZ5"></xref>.}}
      \item
      <ul>
        {{(a)}}
        \item The proof consists of the following computations:
        <ul>
          \item <m>[ 1 ]^2 = [ 1 ]</m>
          \item <m>[ 2 ]^2 = [ 4 ]</m>
          \item <m>[ 3 ]^2 = [ 9 ] = [ 4 ]</m>
          \item <m>[ 4 ]^2 = [ 16 ] = [ 1 ]</m>.
        </ul>
      </ul>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      {{ <xref ref="exer_sec74cong3"></xref>.}}
      \item
      <ul>
        {{(a)}}
        \item Prove the contrapositive by calculating <m>[ a ]^2 + [ b ]^2</m> for all nonzero <m>[ a ]</m> and <m>[ b ]</m> in <m>\Z_3</m>.
      </ul>
    </ul>
